it.emarolab.scene_identification_tracking.semanticSceneLibrary.objects

Interface Array3D.SemanticMap.Resources<D extends Semantics.Descriptor,T>

  • Type Parameters:
    D - the class to refer to, for manipulating the semantic structure. It must extends: Semantics.Descriptor.
    T - the type of the semantic property that map a single component of the array.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Array3D.SemanticMap<D>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MOR3DArray
    Enclosing interface:
    Array3D.SemanticMap<D extends Semantics.Descriptor>

    public static interface Array3D.SemanticMap.Resources<D extends Semantics.Descriptor,T>
extends Array3D.SemanticMap<D>
    The base interface for specifying the specific semantic of a 3D array to be mapped from the Array3D.SemanticMap.

    It describes three properties of type 'T' (e.g.: OWL data properties) where each of them map an Array component: X, Y, Z. Moreover, it defines method for checking if such property exists. This is done to set it with default values later, if not given by the user.
